1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,580
This series is crafted for the purpose of entertainment.

2
00:00:02,580 --> 00:00:04,820
All characters, behaviours, settings, and events depicted in this drama are entirely fictitious.

3
00:00:04,820 --> 00:00:06,660
They are not designed to allude to any particular entity, occupation, or group of people.

4
00:00:06,660 --> 00:00:09,980
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:10,020 --> 00:00:12,620
[North Star Entertainment]

6
00:00:26,180 --> 00:00:32,220
♫I never know what love is like♫

7
00:00:32,220 --> 00:00:37,020
♫All my life, never once have I experienced it♫

8
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:40,340
♫No one to take that place in my heart♫

9
00:00:41,580 --> 00:00:47,580
♫But now that I’ve met you, my heart begins to glow♫

10
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:52,340
♫What feeling is this? Why is my heart fluttering?♫

11
00:00:52,340 --> 00:00:56,460
♫And I just can’t control it.♫

12
00:00:56,460 --> 00:01:00,300
♫What happened to my heart right now?♫

13
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:04,140
♫I can’t control it when you’re around♫

14
00:01:04,140 --> 00:01:10,300
♫This heart…it stops at you♫

15
00:01:11,140 --> 00:01:15,340
♫ Is this love? Is that what they call it?♫

16
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:18,740
♫ When my heart starts to waver♫

17
00:01:18,740 --> 00:01:23,380
♫ Like a stream of water slowly pouring over my heart♫

18
00:01:23,380 --> 00:01:26,460
♫ From dusk till dawn, you’re never far from my sight♫

19
00:01:26,460 --> 00:01:30,860
♫ Or is this love? Are you that someone...♫

20
00:01:30,860 --> 00:01:34,340
♫ ...who’s destined to be with me?♫

21
00:01:34,340 --> 00:01:40,500
♫ Is this really happening ? I really want to know ♫

22
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:41,740
♫‘Cos you now hold a special place in my heart♫

23
00:01:41,740 --> 00:01:46,420
[Waves of Deception]
♫‘Cos you now hold a special place in my heart♫

24
00:01:47,460 --> 00:01:50,140
[Previously]
[Nate]: Do you swear it’s only about work?

25
00:01:50,140 --> 00:01:53,940
Isn’t it because you’ve already fallen into your own trap?

26
00:01:53,940 --> 00:01:55,539
[Lada]: I chose this one.

27
00:01:55,539 --> 00:01:56,780
Isn’t too simple?

28
00:01:56,780 --> 00:01:59,460
[Lada]: That’s why it’s interesting.

29
00:01:59,460 --> 00:02:02,020
[Adisorn]: If one day, you ever meet someone…

30
00:02:02,020 --> 00:02:04,580
who can make your heart flutter,

31
00:02:04,580 --> 00:02:07,220
that person is someone you should cherish for life.

32
00:02:07,220 --> 00:02:11,180
I’m going to make you say it out loud that I’m good at my job.

33
00:02:11,180 --> 00:02:12,780
I’ll be waiting.

34
00:02:12,780 --> 00:02:13,700
[Lada]: You want me to…

35
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:15,820
[Pheempat]: Sabotage Chef Ian’s food.

36
00:02:15,820 --> 00:02:18,300
And blame it all on the Watin Group.

37
00:02:18,300 --> 00:02:19,500
If it were you,

38
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:21,660
will you choose being right or being preferred?

39
00:02:21,660 --> 00:02:22,940
Being right.

40
00:02:23,300 --> 00:02:26,260
[Lada]: But sometimes, being preferred is important too.

41
00:02:30,760 --> 00:02:31,740
All done, Miss.

42
00:02:32,530 --> 00:02:33,329
Thank you.

43
00:02:38,460 --> 00:02:40,060
It’s time, Boss.

44
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:02,980
Today will be the best day for all of us.

45
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:26,620
Hello, everyone. I’m Apo Watinwanich,

46
00:03:26,980 --> 00:03:31,780
Executive President of Monarch Global International Hotel.

47
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:37,860
As you might already know, recently the Watin Group has had the honour to welcome a famous chef…

48
00:03:38,260 --> 00:03:42,700
renowned not only among our country but also across Asia.

49
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:48,140
And I believe she will soon earn herself an international title as a world-class chef.

50
00:03:48,140 --> 00:03:53,140
Without further ado, please give it up and welcome Chef Ian.

51
00:04:11,060 --> 00:04:12,300
This is Chef Ian.

52
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:16,500
She’ll be working with us to create a signature menu for the Watin Group.

53
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:18,300
Please get ready, Chef.

54
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:26,380
I believe you all must be wondering now what the Watin Group’s signature is.

55
00:04:26,660 --> 00:04:30,900
I’m sure everyone will find it surprising once I say it…

56
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:33,020
because it sounds very plain and simple.

57
00:04:33,380 --> 00:04:37,220
But every day of our life, we already have a lot to worry about.

58
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:42,260
So, when it comes to eating, we wouldn’t want to spend much time thinking about it.

59
00:04:43,020 --> 00:04:48,100
Are you getting sick of asking yourself this question–“What should I eat for dinner?”

60
00:04:54,530 --> 00:04:55,930
I chose this one.

61
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:58,300
Isn’t it too simple?

62
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:04,140
Because it’s simple, that’s why it’s interesting.

63
00:05:04,900 --> 00:05:08,020
Everyday, we already have to go through a busy and hectic life all day long.

64
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:11,300
Then, we still have to think about what to have for dinner.

65
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:15,500
Why don’t we try something simple and not complicated?

66
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:17,700
Make an ordinary thing special.

67
00:05:17,700 --> 00:05:21,900
Make a lasting impression for our guests, so that they’d want to come back.

68
00:05:22,700 --> 00:05:25,420
That’s my idea.

69
00:05:28,330 --> 00:05:30,460
Please go ahead with your creation.

70
00:05:48,330 --> 00:05:50,220
I’m going home, sweetie.

71
00:05:50,659 --> 00:05:53,540
Please take good care of yourself, Lada.

72
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:55,420
Work hard.

73
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,540
And don’t let Pat down, okay?

74
00:05:58,860 --> 00:06:00,130
Yes, Mum.

75
00:06:50,580 --> 00:06:51,980
- It’s done.
- Okay.

76
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:56,460
This menu is Seafood Bucket.

77
00:06:56,900 --> 00:07:01,460
But we’ve given it a special name called ’’The Lively Sea”.

78
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:11,300
Such a plain menu yet flavourful and simply delicious.

79
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:15,660
If you want to try it, you must come to our hotel only.

80
00:07:17,860 --> 00:07:20,700
In a minute, our staff will be serving this special dish to all of you.

81
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:21,780
Why are you hiding when the best part is about to come?

82
00:08:26,260 --> 00:08:30,340
Boss, why are you here?

83
00:08:31,060 --> 00:08:32,900
It’s me who should ask you that.

84
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:35,900
What’s a foodie girl like you doing out here…

85
00:08:36,460 --> 00:08:39,220
when the guests are trying out our new menu?

86
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,000
Here, try it.

87
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:55,300
You brought it for me?

88
00:08:58,160 --> 00:08:59,500
Are you all right?

89
00:09:03,860 --> 00:09:04,660
Yes.

90
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:11,060
Don’t you want to try it?

91
00:09:13,860 --> 00:09:15,220
Maybe later.

92
00:09:15,860 --> 00:09:17,960
I still have to go help Miss Preem inside.

93
00:09:18,930 --> 00:09:19,730
Please excuse me then.

94
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:25,580
Is the sea tired? Why isn’t it cheerful?

95
00:09:29,730 --> 00:09:30,530
Yes?

96
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:38,860
If you’re tired, you can take a break. I wouldn’t mind at all.

97
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:42,860
I’m not tired.

98
00:09:43,140 --> 00:09:46,780
I’m actually happy that the outcome is worth the effort.

99
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:51,220
Are you happy with it, Boss?

100
00:09:57,330 --> 00:09:58,130
I think so.

101
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:02,460
But there’re things that need to be improved for next time.

102
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:06,100
That answer sounds so you, Boss.

103
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,500
You did a great job today.

104
00:10:15,980 --> 00:10:16,700
Yes?

105
00:10:19,730 --> 00:10:20,780
Chonlada,

106
00:10:22,260 --> 00:10:23,380
well done.

107
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:36,560
A girl like you who doesn’t know how to work should better keep your mouth shut.

108
00:10:39,100 --> 00:10:42,800
At first, when Boss told me you’d be my assistant;

109
00:10:44,330 --> 00:10:47,340
to be honest, I had so many doubts in mind.

110
00:10:48,100 --> 00:10:52,020
Boss doesn’t usually let anyone work closely with her.

111
00:10:52,980 --> 00:10:57,500
But why is it that she easily agreed and let you do it?

112
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:06,060
You’ve only been working here for a few weeks and haven’t done anything much.

113
00:11:06,730 --> 00:11:10,700
It might be too fast to expect a compliment from me.

114
00:11:11,930 --> 00:11:13,100
I know.

115
00:11:13,740 --> 00:11:19,740
Preem told me it took you almost a year to compliment her.

116
00:11:21,100 --> 00:11:24,740
But for you, it’ll probably take years.

117
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:35,700
Or you’re just doing it to give yourself an excuse for not telling your brother about Chef Ian…

118
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:37,820
because your boss didn't do anything wrong,

119
00:11:37,820 --> 00:11:42,420
and because you’re falling into your own trap.

120
00:11:57,330 --> 00:12:01,340
I just gave you a compliment.

121
00:12:02,820 --> 00:12:04,820
Why are you crying?

122
00:12:43,730 --> 00:12:47,580
I don’t have a handkerchief.

123
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:51,340
Wipe your tears on my shirt instead then.

124
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:07,940
Are you okay?

125
00:13:09,060 --> 00:13:11,560
You were just crying earlier but now you’re laughing.

126
00:13:13,130 --> 00:13:15,460
Thank you…for the answer you gave me that day.

127
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:19,200
What day?

128
00:13:19,700 --> 00:13:23,600
That day when you told me to choose between the preferred suit or the right suit.

129
00:13:25,730 --> 00:13:31,340
You made me realise something and decided to go for that answer.

130
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:33,200
What answer?

131
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:12,220
At first, I was too scared to choose.

132
00:14:14,660 --> 00:14:18,800
But then your words of advice helped me make up my mind.

133
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,460
And I sure made the right choice.

134
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:30,000
Thank you.

135
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:13,140
Oh, there they are!

136
00:15:17,060 --> 00:15:18,300
What is it, Dad?

137
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:20,700
Can I borrow your assistant for a while?

138
00:15:20,860 --> 00:15:21,660
Come, Lada.

139
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:24,760
What for, Dad?

140
00:15:25,300 --> 00:15:26,960
Probably to pair her up with someone.

141
00:15:29,130 --> 00:15:29,930
Let’s go, Lada.

142
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:32,500
Why are you blocking me?

143
00:15:33,300 --> 00:15:35,260
I’m only borrowing her for a few minutes.

144
00:15:35,460 --> 00:15:36,580
It won’t be long.

145
00:15:37,460 --> 00:15:38,820
Long or not, you can’t take her anyway.

146
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:40,760
As her boss,

147
00:15:41,300 --> 00:15:44,780
I can’t allow her to do anything nonsense other than work.

148
00:15:45,380 --> 00:15:46,540
Let’s go.

149
00:15:46,730 --> 00:15:47,530
Boss!

150
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:50,300
We have a problem.

151
00:15:50,860 --> 00:15:51,620
What happened?

152
00:15:52,300 --> 00:15:54,160
Those guests who ate Chef Ian’s food.

153
00:15:54,330 --> 00:15:56,930
They suddenly vomited and got an upset stomach.

154
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:01,660
Ouch!

155
00:16:02,530 --> 00:16:04,420
Uncle! What’s wrong?

156
00:16:04,420 --> 00:16:05,300
Uncle!

157
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:08,020
Dad! Dad.

158
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:09,300
Are you all right?

159
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:11,260
- Uncle.
- Are you okay?

160
00:16:29,100 --> 00:16:30,900
Please have a seat first.

161
00:16:31,260 --> 00:16:32,200
Oh, that’s all right.

162
00:16:32,700 --> 00:16:34,130
How’s he doing?

163
00:16:34,260 --> 00:16:35,200
Just a moment please.

164
00:16:36,260 --> 00:16:37,900
Did you get some sleep?

165
00:16:43,260 --> 00:16:45,700
Looks like you didn’t get any sleep either.

166
00:16:47,100 --> 00:16:52,060
Miss Preem told me you were at the hospital all night,

167
00:16:52,060 --> 00:16:54,340
following up on every guest’s condition.

168
00:16:55,160 --> 00:16:56,560
So, did you get any sleep?

169
00:16:58,400 --> 00:17:00,220
Don’t worry, it’s my job anyway.

170
00:17:01,330 --> 00:17:03,930
How is Big Boss doing?

171
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:18,000
Hello.

172
00:17:31,730 --> 00:17:32,730
I’m so sorry.

173
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:35,500
Sorry about what?

174
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:43,400
Hello?

175
00:17:44,460 --> 00:17:46,900
It was you, wasn’t it?

176
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:50,340
Hold on, Lada. What are you talking about?

177
00:17:50,340 --> 00:17:52,220
Poisoning the food at the event.

178
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:53,980
You did it, didn’t you?

179
00:17:55,100 --> 00:17:57,760
Lada, it was you who did that.

180
00:17:58,160 --> 00:18:01,300
Impossible. I already threw it away.

181
00:18:01,460 --> 00:18:03,220
So, you betrayed me?

182
00:18:03,220 --> 00:18:05,420
You refused to help our family’s hotel?

183
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:09,220
I’m so sorry.

184
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:12,930
But I just couldn’t do it.

185
00:18:13,160 --> 00:18:16,860
It wasn’t right, Pat. You’re not playing it fair.

186
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:21,220
If you didn’t do it, then it was probably someone else.

187
00:18:21,760 --> 00:18:27,580
Someone else? You also sent someone to work here apart from me?

188
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:30,580
Don’t let me down again.

189
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:33,900
Because the Watin Group won’t be losing only their name next time.

190
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:35,780
I’ll make them lose something else too.

191
00:18:38,960 --> 00:18:39,940
Pat!

192
00:18:56,460 --> 00:18:59,130
Boss trusted me to take care of this event.

193
00:18:59,560 --> 00:19:03,000
But I failed to protect our hotel’s guests and reputation.

194
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:06,560
I’m really sorry.

195
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:11,220
Nam said the police have already looked into it.

196
00:19:11,860 --> 00:19:17,500
The cause of food poisoning mainly comes from the ice being contaminated.

197
00:19:18,380 --> 00:19:20,900
It’s not your fault, Lada.

198
00:19:21,540 --> 00:19:22,900
You don’t have to apologise.

199
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:34,740
But if I had been more careful, something terrible like this wouldn’t have happened.

200
00:19:38,860 --> 00:19:44,180
Do you know what I had to go through for the Watin Group to come this far?

201
00:19:44,580 --> 00:19:49,900
It wasn’t easy at all. I’ve met all kinds of people.

202
00:19:50,260 --> 00:19:55,060
And for someone like you, I can see through it all.

203
00:19:55,500 --> 00:20:00,060
I have absolutely no doubt that you've done all you can to protect us, the Watin Group.

204
00:20:07,160 --> 00:20:11,740
If you really feel guilty, you should go home and rest.

205
00:20:13,900 --> 00:20:15,130
I’m giving you a day off.

206
00:20:17,730 --> 00:20:19,220
Don’t come to work today.

207
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:21,360
Boss.

208
00:20:22,060 --> 00:20:26,100
All the guests who attended the event are safe now.

209
00:20:26,560 --> 00:20:29,420
And I still have a lot more work for you to do.

210
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:34,940
If my assistant gets so stressed out and falls sick, how do you expect me to focus on work then?

211
00:20:40,460 --> 00:20:42,260
Just admit you’re worried about her.

212
00:20:43,530 --> 00:20:45,540
Stop using work as an excuse.

213
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:47,460
Dad.

214
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:52,260
Jimlim, is Fah here yet?

215
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:53,780
I’ll get her for you, sir.

216
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:58,420
Oh, there she is.

217
00:20:59,360 --> 00:21:01,130
The doctor is here, Uncle.

218
00:21:02,760 --> 00:21:05,100
Hello, Uncle. How are you feeling?

219
00:21:05,930 --> 00:21:06,820
Much better.

220
00:21:08,340 --> 00:21:12,220
This is Trai. He’s the son of Chaiyuth,

221
00:21:12,660 --> 00:21:14,540
the doctor who used to take care of me.

222
00:21:17,060 --> 00:21:22,460
Trai, this is Lada, the girl I said I’d like to introduce to you last night.

223
00:21:24,130 --> 00:21:26,420
Very nice to meet you, Miss Chonlada.

224
00:21:29,530 --> 00:21:33,340
Finally, you two met.

225
00:21:45,700 --> 00:21:50,140
Boss, your dad might feel crossed if you suddenly leave like this.

226
00:21:50,140 --> 00:21:54,020
Let him be. It’s better than having you do something you don’t want to.

227
00:21:54,420 --> 00:21:56,220
Or are you afraid you’ll be in trouble?

228
00:21:57,130 --> 00:21:58,780
No, it’s not like that.

229
00:21:58,780 --> 00:22:02,260
I just don’t want you and Big Boss to have a quarrel.

230
00:22:03,930 --> 00:22:07,540
Hurry up and get in the car. Dad and I usually argue all the time.

231
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:09,180
But…

232
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:11,540
Or do you still want to talk to Trai?

233
00:22:11,930 --> 00:22:13,980
Should I take you back inside?

234
00:22:15,260 --> 00:22:16,380
What does he have to do with this?

235
00:22:16,600 --> 00:22:20,500
If not, then get in the car. I’ll drop you off at the condo.

236
00:22:21,560 --> 00:22:23,540
It’s okay, I can go back myself.

237
00:22:24,060 --> 00:22:25,740
Please go get some rest, Boss.

238
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:37,100
Okay, fine! I get it.

239
00:22:49,400 --> 00:22:52,980
If I let you go back alone, do you think I’ll be able to sleep?

240
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:54,500
I’ll drive you home.

241
00:23:08,100 --> 00:23:10,620
I think she’s getting serious this time.

242
00:23:13,330 --> 00:23:16,360
Yeah, it's all up to Lada now.

243
00:23:44,360 --> 00:23:45,160
Yes?

244
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:51,360
How did you know?

245
00:23:54,100 --> 00:23:55,540
What are you doing?

246
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:06,500
Pat! Pat!

247
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:21,420
Is there something wrong?

248
00:24:46,900 --> 00:24:48,660
Nothing. Let’s go.

249
00:25:11,930 --> 00:25:13,780
Hey, wrong building. That way.

250
00:25:18,200 --> 00:25:19,980
It’s nothing. Let’s go.

251
00:25:26,760 --> 00:25:27,730
Look out, Boss!

252
00:25:28,900 --> 00:25:29,980
Look out, Boss!

253
00:25:33,330 --> 00:25:34,460
Are you okay?

254
00:25:39,530 --> 00:25:41,140
Are you all right, Chonlada?

255
00:25:42,160 --> 00:25:44,580
We’re…we’re here?

256
00:25:46,960 --> 00:25:48,900
You don’t have to walk me to my room.

257
00:25:48,930 --> 00:25:50,530
I can go up there myself.

258
00:25:50,730 --> 00:25:52,100
Thank you for driving me.

259
00:26:00,500 --> 00:26:02,460
Wait, Chonlada.

260
00:26:02,460 --> 00:26:03,860
Boss, why did you get out?

261
00:26:05,060 --> 00:26:07,740
Well, I…

262
00:26:31,580 --> 00:26:32,980
Look out!

263
00:26:38,500 --> 00:26:39,700
Pizza?

264
00:26:44,500 --> 00:26:45,400
Are you okay?

265
00:26:49,330 --> 00:26:50,130
What’s wrong?

266
00:26:50,530 --> 00:26:57,140
I’m sorry. I told you to stay in the car.

267
00:26:58,260 --> 00:27:00,540
Please leave now, Boss. Go home. Go.

268
00:27:00,540 --> 00:27:01,300
Hold on!

269
00:27:05,900 --> 00:27:06,980
I’m hungry.

270
00:27:17,940 --> 00:27:20,980
Boss, can you wait here first?

271
00:27:22,800 --> 00:27:25,580
Why? Is your room untidy?

272
00:27:25,860 --> 00:27:31,140
No, it’s not. I just need to take care of something first.

273
00:27:37,800 --> 00:27:39,020
Please wait a second.

274
00:28:05,600 --> 00:28:06,700
It’s done.

275
00:28:09,600 --> 00:28:10,400
Please come in.

276
00:28:24,900 --> 00:28:27,780
All I have now is instant noodles.

277
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:31,660
They’re full of sodium so I’m not sure if you can eat them.

278
00:28:32,760 --> 00:28:33,560
Of course, I can.

279
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:37,180
Which flavour do you want?

280
00:28:37,700 --> 00:28:39,220
I have plenty for you to choose from.

281
00:28:43,260 --> 00:28:44,740
Which one do you like?

282
00:28:47,930 --> 00:28:49,260
All of them.

283
00:28:49,260 --> 00:28:52,340
Otherwise, I wouldn’t have bought so many.

284
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:58,400
Then, what flavour do you want to eat now?

285
00:29:07,760 --> 00:29:11,620
How about Miso Ramen? It’s not spicy. You can surely have it.

286
00:29:14,130 --> 00:29:15,360
How hungry are you?

287
00:29:15,960 --> 00:29:18,500
Can you wait? I’m going to make one at a time.

288
00:29:23,900 --> 00:29:27,420
Let’s make two at once.

289
00:29:27,420 --> 00:29:29,380
Then we can share.

290
00:29:47,800 --> 00:29:49,500
I guess food can really help.

291
00:29:51,400 --> 00:29:52,200
Yes?

292
00:29:52,900 --> 00:29:53,700
What did you say?

293
00:29:56,730 --> 00:29:59,020
You’ve been acting quite weird since downstairs.

294
00:29:59,020 --> 00:30:00,180
Are you all right?

295
00:30:03,940 --> 00:30:09,300
I’m just still worried about what happened this morning.

296
00:30:09,300 --> 00:30:11,540
I’m worried Chef Ian might be upset.

297
00:30:13,700 --> 00:30:15,540
I wonder who wouldn’t be.

298
00:30:16,700 --> 00:30:19,740
All the guests at the event had an upset stomach.

299
00:30:19,740 --> 00:30:22,060
They probably believe it’s because of Chef Ian’s food.

300
00:30:23,300 --> 00:30:27,460
Will Chef Ian still agree to work with us then?

301
00:30:31,660 --> 00:30:33,820
She actually wanted to cancel it at first.

302
00:30:34,700 --> 00:30:38,980
What happened earlier has somehow ruined her reputation and discredited her.

303
00:30:42,530 --> 00:30:44,500
But I already talked to her this morning.

304
00:30:45,700 --> 00:30:47,700
Our hotel will arrange a press conference…

305
00:30:48,160 --> 00:30:49,820
and take sole responsibility for everything.

306
00:30:50,300 --> 00:30:52,460
We’ll also tell the press that it’s all our fault.

307
00:30:55,200 --> 00:31:01,160
So the actual cause doesn’t come from the ice but the food?

308
00:31:04,860 --> 00:31:06,140
Not the food.

309
00:31:08,660 --> 00:31:11,380
But from the substance contaminated in the food.

310
00:31:13,930 --> 00:31:16,060
Did someone poison the food?

311
00:31:17,330 --> 00:31:19,780
Do you know who did it?

312
00:31:20,300 --> 00:31:24,340
After checking the CCTV, some of our staff could be on a suspect list.

313
00:31:25,500 --> 00:31:29,940
But it’d take some time to investigate and confirm who actually did it,

314
00:31:31,530 --> 00:31:35,820
what they did it for, or who ordered them to do it.

315
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:06,300
Does it feel better?

316
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:16,000
It’s all right. I’m used to it. I often cook at home.

317
00:32:17,500 --> 00:32:19,820
Why don’t you go and sit on the couch first?

318
00:32:20,220 --> 00:32:22,340
I’ll bring it to you once it’s done.

319
00:32:24,860 --> 00:32:27,780
It’s okay. Let me help you with it.

320
00:32:28,130 --> 00:32:32,200
No need. You’re the guest, Boss. Let me take care of you.

321
00:32:44,500 --> 00:32:46,700
Geez, that hurts.

322
00:33:08,060 --> 00:33:08,860
Let me help.

323
00:33:09,260 --> 00:33:11,200
It’s okay. Let me do it.

324
00:33:11,300 --> 00:33:12,180
It’s okay.

325
00:33:12,260 --> 00:33:13,060
Give it to me.

326
00:33:14,620 --> 00:33:16,660
I’ll get a new one for you.

327
00:33:35,160 --> 00:33:35,960
Here you go.

328
00:33:41,860 --> 00:33:42,660
Just a second, Boss.

329
00:34:00,930 --> 00:34:04,900
Now, we can eat while looking at the stars. Quite a happy meal, isn’t it?

330
00:34:11,219 --> 00:34:15,300
By the way, there are still some left if you want more. I made loads of them.

331
00:34:40,219 --> 00:34:42,980
Why are you sitting on the floor, Boss?

332
00:34:46,780 --> 00:34:48,020
But you’re also not sitting on a couch.

333
00:34:48,460 --> 00:34:51,100
I’m comfier this way.

334
00:34:54,100 --> 00:34:55,699
I like it here too.

335
00:35:01,160 --> 00:35:04,900
Now I know why you and Big Boss often argue.

336
00:35:06,500 --> 00:35:09,360
It’s because you’re so stubborn like a mule.

337
00:35:13,730 --> 00:35:15,540
I probably got it from you.

338
00:35:19,060 --> 00:35:21,380
Are you saying I’m stubborn?

339
00:35:32,460 --> 00:35:34,020
This noodle is quite good.

340
00:35:36,760 --> 00:35:40,820
That means you’re opening up for a plain and useless thing.

341
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:47,020
It’s because you made them.

342
00:36:25,700 --> 00:36:28,940
Oh, I…I forgot to give you something to drink.

343
00:36:29,260 --> 00:36:32,420
I’ll get some water for you.

344
00:36:39,300 --> 00:36:41,300
I’m sorry, Boss! I didn’t mean it!

345
00:36:43,300 --> 00:36:45,020
I’m so sorry, Boss!

346
00:36:45,380 --> 00:36:47,820
Oh my gosh, I’m sorry.

347
00:36:49,960 --> 00:36:51,300
I’m so sorry.

348
00:36:54,600 --> 00:36:55,400
I’m sorry.

349
00:37:02,960 --> 00:37:06,300
Why don’t you get some cloth to wipe it instead, Chonlada?

350
00:37:09,260 --> 00:37:10,340
Okay.

351
00:37:22,560 --> 00:37:23,360
Nam!

352
00:37:25,400 --> 00:37:26,200
Nam!

353
00:37:29,740 --> 00:37:31,140
Why are you looking so pretty today?

354
00:37:33,330 --> 00:37:35,740
But this wasn’t what you were wearing when you left home.

355
00:37:40,330 --> 00:37:41,960
They’re Chonlada’s.

356
00:37:42,460 --> 00:37:43,260
Huh?

357
00:37:43,360 --> 00:37:44,580
Hang on.

358
00:37:44,580 --> 00:37:46,940
It’s not what I think it is, is it?

359
00:37:48,200 --> 00:37:50,530
I had a little accident.

360
00:37:52,300 --> 00:37:53,530
What happened?

361
00:37:55,060 --> 00:37:58,180
I was eating noodles and spilled them on my shirt.

362
00:37:58,660 --> 00:37:59,530
Where did you eat them?

363
00:38:00,060 --> 00:38:01,940
And why do you have to change into her clothes?

364
00:38:05,500 --> 00:38:06,300
Her room.

365
00:38:07,400 --> 00:38:08,200
Her room?

366
00:38:11,700 --> 00:38:12,860
Don’t imagine things.

367
00:38:13,960 --> 00:38:15,380
Nothing happened.

368
00:38:15,380 --> 00:38:18,000
Okay, that’s good then.

369
00:38:18,530 --> 00:38:21,900
This means I can still pair Lada up with Trai.

370
00:38:24,300 --> 00:38:28,820
It’s nothing for now. But there might be something in the future.

371
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:31,260
What was that again?

372
00:38:34,800 --> 00:38:37,100
Tell Dad to tell that doctor Trai…

373
00:38:38,060 --> 00:38:42,820
that from now on, Chonlada won’t have time for anyone.

374
00:38:43,560 --> 00:38:46,660
Oooh, really?

375
00:38:48,260 --> 00:38:52,340
♫ You’re the one that change my life ♫

376
00:38:53,020 --> 00:38:56,900
♫ Make me feel more important than anyone♫
Give me five!

377
00:38:56,900 --> 00:38:59,620
♫ Thank you so much♫

378
00:38:59,620 --> 00:39:02,900
♫ For making my life meaningful♫

379
00:39:02,900 --> 00:39:09,100
♫ How lucky I am to have you♫

380
00:39:21,530 --> 00:39:22,600
Good morning.

381
00:39:59,660 --> 00:40:00,780
Chonlada.

382
00:40:04,560 --> 00:40:05,360
Boss.

383
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:07,500
When did you get here?

384
00:40:08,130 --> 00:40:09,900
I’ve been waiting here for a while.

385
00:40:10,360 --> 00:40:12,780
But you were too busy with your phone.

386
00:40:12,800 --> 00:40:14,060
And didn’t look up at all.

387
00:40:17,200 --> 00:40:19,300
Why would you want to see me, Boss?

388
00:40:20,700 --> 00:40:22,580
I need to talk to you.

389
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:26,420
About what?

390
00:40:33,260 --> 00:40:35,420
Are you looking for someone?

391
00:40:38,930 --> 00:40:43,860
No. So, what do you want to talk to me about?

392
00:40:46,660 --> 00:40:47,730
Let’s talk in the car.

393
00:40:48,730 --> 00:40:49,380
Yes?

394
00:40:50,130 --> 00:40:50,930
Get in the car.

395
00:41:23,330 --> 00:41:25,060
Are you afraid someone might follow?

396
00:41:25,660 --> 00:41:28,260
You keep looking around nervously.

397
00:41:28,960 --> 00:41:33,600
It’s nothing. So, why do you want to talk to me?

398
00:41:39,900 --> 00:41:41,140
Eat something first.

399
00:41:45,800 --> 00:41:47,180
They’re from my dad.

400
00:41:52,060 --> 00:41:53,340
Thank you.

401
00:42:26,530 --> 00:42:27,360
Is it not good?

402
00:42:33,530 --> 00:42:37,900
If you bought it, please tell the shop to improve their sauce a little.

403
00:42:42,360 --> 00:42:43,860
I’ll let them know.

404
00:42:47,300 --> 00:42:50,700
But they seem to put their heart into making it.

405
00:43:19,260 --> 00:43:22,660
Yesterday, when you told me about,

406
00:43:22,660 --> 00:43:25,700
our staff being interrogated,

407
00:43:26,100 --> 00:43:28,140
can you tell me who they are?

408
00:43:29,360 --> 00:43:30,800
I’m afraid I can’t.

409
00:43:32,140 --> 00:43:33,130
Why?

410
00:43:33,900 --> 00:43:36,140
It’s still under investigation.

411
00:43:36,420 --> 00:43:38,580
We still can’t confirm who actually did it.

412
00:43:38,860 --> 00:43:43,380
If I give you the names but it turns out they didn’t do it, those people might have a hard time working here after that.

413
00:43:43,930 --> 00:43:48,340
Does that mean those who are being interrogated are our hotel’s employees?

414
00:43:49,600 --> 00:43:50,730
Why would you want to know?

415
00:43:51,530 --> 00:43:52,930
I’m just curious.

416
00:43:53,400 --> 00:43:55,980
So, what is it that you want to talk to me about?

417
00:43:57,380 --> 00:43:59,060
- Well, I…
- Sis!

418
00:43:59,740 --> 00:44:01,460
Miss you so much!

419
00:44:01,460 --> 00:44:03,560
Fai, how did you get here?

420
00:44:04,260 --> 00:44:06,340
I came to Chumphon yesterday to take care of something.

421
00:44:06,340 --> 00:44:08,860
And I thought maybe I should stop by to see you before I go home.

422
00:44:10,000 --> 00:44:11,500
You and Lom are the same.

423
00:44:11,800 --> 00:44:13,660
Never told me beforehand.

424
00:44:14,000 --> 00:44:17,260
Unlike your big sister. Din always let me know before she’d come.

425
00:44:18,420 --> 00:44:19,580
There you go again.

426
00:44:26,860 --> 00:44:28,500
This is Miss Chonlada.

427
00:44:29,330 --> 00:44:31,860
This is Atchima, my little sister.

428
00:44:33,100 --> 00:44:34,740
Miss Chonlada?

429
00:44:35,660 --> 00:44:38,220
Is she the girl Lom said is your girlfriend?

430
00:44:45,930 --> 00:44:47,530
We’re just colleagues.

431
00:44:48,200 --> 00:44:49,560
Nothing more than that.

432
00:44:52,800 --> 00:44:56,300
About that work you want me to do, I’ll get it done as soon as possible.

433
00:45:10,900 --> 00:45:11,980
What?

434
00:45:23,700 --> 00:45:25,860
Pat, where are you?

435
00:45:26,300 --> 00:45:27,940
I’m exactly where I should be.

436
00:45:28,260 --> 00:45:30,460
Why do you sound so serious?

437
00:45:31,360 --> 00:45:33,460
That’s because I couldn’t get a hold of you.

438
00:45:33,500 --> 00:45:37,020
So, you just told everyone you and your boss are only colleagues?

439
00:45:37,620 --> 00:45:39,780
Do you think that’d help?

440
00:45:42,660 --> 00:45:46,620
You’re wondering which one is the mole, aren’t you?

441
00:45:49,460 --> 00:45:52,020
Pat, I’m begging you.

442
00:45:52,420 --> 00:45:57,140
You’re smart and talented. That’s why you’re able to look after our hotel and make it this far.

443
00:45:58,000 --> 00:45:59,730
Please don’t stoop so low.

444
00:46:00,100 --> 00:46:05,180
Hearing you said that, I’m completely convinced that your lady boss is so important to you.

445
00:46:06,200 --> 00:46:07,900
It’s not what you think.

446
00:46:08,220 --> 00:46:09,660
Boss and I are…

447
00:46:19,820 --> 00:46:23,460
What? If you and Miss Chonlada are just colleagues,

448
00:46:23,460 --> 00:46:25,260
does that mean Lom only imagined it?

449
00:46:26,560 --> 00:46:30,220
You know what she’s like. Always imagine things and overreact.

450
00:46:30,530 --> 00:46:33,140
But she looks so hurt and frustrated this time.

451
00:46:33,160 --> 00:46:36,020
She even flew all the way there just to vent it out on me.

452
00:46:36,160 --> 00:46:41,180
That’s why I have to come here for once to see the face of a girl who could make Lom so desperate like that.

453
00:46:43,500 --> 00:46:48,380
But judging from your reaction…You too, right?

454
00:46:49,660 --> 00:46:52,020
Maybe Lom isn’t the only one who feels it.

455
00:46:55,600 --> 00:46:58,420
You’ve just arrived. Why don’t you get some rest first?

456
00:47:00,500 --> 00:47:01,820
You feel it too, don’t you?

457
00:47:05,200 --> 00:47:07,220
I already told you. Chonlada and I are just colleagues.

458
00:47:07,220 --> 00:47:09,220
What do you want me to feel about her?

459
00:47:10,660 --> 00:47:14,900
I don’t know about Miss Chonlada, but for you…

460
00:47:15,500 --> 00:47:18,460
If you don’t feel anything for her, why did you tell Lom that she can’t pursue Miss Chonlada?

461
00:47:21,100 --> 00:47:23,420
Do you have a secret crush on her?

462
00:47:25,900 --> 00:47:29,580
If you don’t want to go back to your room, you can hang around here

463
00:47:30,930 --> 00:47:32,260
I have work to do.

464
00:47:35,130 --> 00:47:36,800
Not so fast.

465
00:47:40,730 --> 00:47:41,530
Ouch!

466
00:47:43,160 --> 00:47:47,340
Aww, did you just blush?

467
00:47:54,200 --> 00:47:58,340
Din, if you’re not busy, find some time to come to Hua Hin with Boss Rose.

468
00:48:02,060 --> 00:48:07,260
You should be able to see the person who can make our Nam divorce with her work.

469
00:48:08,000 --> 00:48:10,460
I’m serious. Come and see it for yourself.

470
00:48:16,140 --> 00:48:18,340
[Boss]

471
00:48:37,800 --> 00:48:38,600
Hello?

472
00:48:57,200 --> 00:48:59,500
Is there something you want to talk to me, Boss?

473
00:49:04,360 --> 00:49:07,500
Are you free this evening after work?

474
00:49:07,860 --> 00:49:10,940
I’d like to take you to try out the food at this restaurant.

475
00:49:11,930 --> 00:49:12,730
I’m not free.

476
00:49:17,160 --> 00:49:19,130
What about tomorrow?

477
00:49:20,000 --> 00:49:21,300
Tomorrow too.

478
00:49:27,930 --> 00:49:29,580
Are you free any day this week?

479
00:49:32,130 --> 00:49:34,860
I’m a little tied up these days.

480
00:49:35,600 --> 00:49:36,760
I’m sorry, Boss.

481
00:49:37,860 --> 00:49:38,660
Hold on.

482
00:49:43,330 --> 00:49:45,380
Have I done anything to upset you?

483
00:49:46,360 --> 00:49:47,220
No.

484
00:49:48,660 --> 00:49:53,620
If that’s all, I’m afraid I have to leave. Miss Preem has asked me to take care of something.

485
00:50:13,400 --> 00:50:14,300
Sis.

486
00:50:15,100 --> 00:50:16,860
You’re looking for me?

487
00:50:17,660 --> 00:50:19,160
Shhh! Keep it down.

488
00:50:20,160 --> 00:50:20,960
What is it?

489
00:50:22,660 --> 00:50:23,460
What is it?

490
00:50:24,260 --> 00:50:27,100
Promise me first, that you won’t tell anyone about it.

491
00:50:29,900 --> 00:50:32,500
Do you want me to sign an NDA too?

492
00:50:33,930 --> 00:50:34,800
I’m serious.

493
00:50:37,130 --> 00:50:40,580
I know, your face just says it all.

494
00:50:41,330 --> 00:50:43,140
It’s about Miss Chonlada, isn’t it?

495
00:50:50,530 --> 00:50:55,380
I just don’t understand. She suddenly acts like she’s mad at me.

496
00:50:57,130 --> 00:51:01,820
But when I asked her what’s wrong or if she has any problem, she kept denying it.

497
00:51:04,260 --> 00:51:05,900
What’s wrong with her, Fah?

498
00:51:07,360 --> 00:51:08,300
I’m totally lost here.

499
00:51:08,960 --> 00:51:11,020
You seem to care about her a lot.

500
00:51:13,700 --> 00:51:16,800
I just don’t want to have problems with my colleagues.

501
00:51:17,760 --> 00:51:22,340
If we’re on bad terms, we’ll surely have a hard time working together.

502
00:51:22,340 --> 00:51:24,860
I don’t want to wait until it’s too late.

503
00:51:25,260 --> 00:51:27,340
She didn’t tell me anything about taking leaves.

504
00:51:27,340 --> 00:51:30,260
She only wrote ‘for personal matters’ on the leave letter.

505
00:51:30,260 --> 00:51:35,300
Usually, she’d always let me know in clear detail where she’d go or what she’d do.

506
00:51:38,260 --> 00:51:40,660
Aww, sis. That’s nothing.

507
00:51:40,660 --> 00:51:44,140
All you have to do is give her a call and ask.

508
00:51:44,140 --> 00:51:45,380
What if she doesn’t tell me?

509
00:51:47,060 --> 00:51:48,330
That’s not a problem either.

510
00:51:52,330 --> 00:51:53,300
You have an idea?

511
00:52:08,900 --> 00:52:12,380
Lada, why didn’t you tell me you’d come home, sweetie?

512
00:52:17,900 --> 00:52:21,180
Mum, has Pat been home lately?

513
00:52:23,330 --> 00:52:25,820
Your dad is also looking for him.

514
00:52:26,300 --> 00:52:28,330
I heard the hotel is having a lot of problems.

515
00:52:29,160 --> 00:52:31,060
No one can get a hold of him.

516
00:52:31,330 --> 00:52:34,160
Your dad told Wat to get Pat to come in for a talk tomorrow.

517
00:52:35,600 --> 00:52:37,360
What does Dad want to talk to him about?

518
00:52:44,730 --> 00:52:45,900
Pat’s phone is off.

519
00:52:48,860 --> 00:52:49,660
Loser.

520
00:52:51,600 --> 00:52:54,060
If that brat wants to keep avoiding me like this…

521
00:52:55,540 --> 00:52:59,540
Wat, just do as I said.

522
00:53:00,400 --> 00:53:03,420
But Dad, are you sure?

523
00:53:04,560 --> 00:53:06,540
Why on earth should I keep it then?

524
00:53:06,700 --> 00:53:08,420
The more we persist, the more money we’d lose.

525
00:53:08,930 --> 00:53:13,820
If he can’t manage just a small hotel branch and even loses to Adisorn’s daughter,

526
00:53:14,700 --> 00:53:17,020
then shut it down and sell the whole thing off!

527
00:53:17,760 --> 00:53:19,620
Do you really have to do that, Dad?

528
00:53:19,900 --> 00:53:21,140
If Pat finds out, he might…

529
00:53:21,200 --> 00:53:26,900
I’m doing this because I want to teach him that being my son means you must always win.

530
00:53:27,540 --> 00:53:29,300
There’s no place for losing.

531
00:53:30,100 --> 00:53:34,140
Especially when he’s losing to a girl like Adisorn’s daughter.

532
00:53:34,740 --> 00:53:37,180
If he still wants to be in a hotel business,

533
00:53:37,180 --> 00:53:40,140
let him beg for a job from that brat’s daughter then.

534
00:53:46,300 --> 00:53:48,360
If Pat knows that Dad’s going to sell it off,

535
00:53:49,360 --> 00:53:50,600
he would never let that happen.

536
00:53:52,060 --> 00:53:53,660
But Dad already made up his mind.

537
00:53:54,400 --> 00:53:55,460
No one can do anything now.

538
00:53:56,860 --> 00:54:00,620
Not really. Pat clearly takes after his father.

539
00:54:01,460 --> 00:54:04,380
They’d rather die than losing their faces.

540
00:54:04,940 --> 00:54:10,100
And now, Pat is like someone who’s striving for his last breath.

541
00:54:10,620 --> 00:54:15,020
I’m sure he’d do anything to keep his hotel going.

542
00:54:36,360 --> 00:54:37,020
Listen,

543
00:54:37,940 --> 00:54:43,100
if you still want more after finishing this one, maybe we should go out for a drink tonight.

544
00:54:46,800 --> 00:54:47,820
Not funny.

545
00:54:49,100 --> 00:54:51,420
Hey, I’m serious.

546
00:54:52,020 --> 00:54:55,100
If staying with the Watin Group makes you so stressed like this,

547
00:54:55,100 --> 00:54:59,140
since your dad is going to sell off your brother’s hotel anyway;

548
00:54:59,380 --> 00:55:01,260
why don’t you just back off?

549
00:55:03,960 --> 00:55:05,300
I can’t.

550
00:55:09,000 --> 00:55:13,380
You’re not falling into your own trap, are you?

551
00:55:23,560 --> 00:55:25,620
It doesn’t matter how I feel.

552
00:55:26,800 --> 00:55:31,400
The point is I can’t leave Boss right now.

553
00:55:32,100 --> 00:55:32,900
Why?

554
00:55:34,660 --> 00:55:38,800
Is there anything you still haven’t told me, Lada?

555
00:55:48,600 --> 00:55:51,300
Hey, Lada.

556
00:55:56,960 --> 00:55:59,580
This one is important. I have to take it.

557
00:56:00,960 --> 00:56:03,100
But I’ll be back to get an answer from you.

558
00:56:05,000 --> 00:56:08,420
You’d better have it ready. I’ll be right back.

559
00:56:52,100 --> 00:56:53,340
Hello, Boss.

560
00:57:04,760 --> 00:57:06,130
Hello, Boss.

561
00:57:08,260 --> 00:57:09,340
How have you been?

562
00:57:10,600 --> 00:57:11,620
I’m good.

563
00:57:59,380 --> 00:58:01,380
[Boss]

564
00:58:21,700 --> 00:58:24,180
[Chonlada]

565
00:59:31,500 --> 00:59:34,660
The work won’t get itself done without putting in any effort

566
00:59:35,860 --> 00:59:37,860
The same also goes with love.

567
00:59:40,360 --> 00:59:41,540
What are you doing here, Dad?

568
00:59:43,360 --> 00:59:45,460
You’ve been looking so depressed for many days now.

569
00:59:45,600 --> 00:59:48,060
At first, I thought I would leave you alone.

570
00:59:48,500 --> 00:59:52,260
But so far, I don’t think anything good will come out of it.

571
00:59:54,560 --> 00:59:58,620
I’m only stressing about work, not about Chonlada.

572
01:00:02,260 --> 01:00:05,580
I haven’t mentioned anything about Lada yet.

573
01:00:07,360 --> 01:00:08,360
Don’t get so defensive.

574
01:00:13,060 --> 01:00:13,900
Geez, Dad!

575
01:00:16,160 --> 01:00:22,780
Fine, if you insist that I should stay out of this…I’ll do that.

576
01:00:25,200 --> 01:00:26,000
Wait, Dad.

577
01:00:30,600 --> 01:00:44,580
I…I just feel that Chonlada is trying to avoid me.

578
01:00:48,200 --> 01:00:54,300
So, do you want me to help or not?

579
01:01:13,460 --> 01:01:19,180
So, for last Monday and Tuesday?

580
01:01:19,400 --> 01:01:21,930
Okay, I’ll bring them down to you in a minute.

581
01:01:26,300 --> 01:01:32,220
Miss Preem, these are documents from the accounting department that you’ve asked me to get from them.

582
01:01:32,530 --> 01:01:35,300
Can you give them to Boss for me?

583
01:01:35,300 --> 01:01:37,180
Can you give them to Boss for me? I have to go talk to Miss Wadee first.

584
01:01:38,660 --> 01:01:41,140
Why don’t you give them to Boss yourself?

585
01:01:41,140 --> 01:01:43,260
I’ll go get Miss Wadee for you.

586
01:01:44,130 --> 01:01:47,760
That’s all right. I’ll be right back. Take care of it for me.

587
01:02:08,530 --> 01:02:10,940
Boss!

588
01:02:10,940 --> 01:02:12,900
What are you doing?

589
01:02:13,000 --> 01:02:13,800
Don’t move.

590
01:02:27,300 --> 01:02:28,800
Why didn’t you answer my call?

591
01:02:30,730 --> 01:02:32,530
I left my phone on the table.

592
01:02:36,900 --> 01:02:38,360
Miss Preem already told me.

593
01:02:39,760 --> 01:02:41,260
That’s why I’ve got this for you.

594
01:02:41,860 --> 01:02:43,220
You should wear it.

595
01:02:43,730 --> 01:02:47,260
It’ll come in handy in case of an emergency or when you forget your phone.

596
01:02:47,800 --> 01:02:50,620
The watch will notify you when there’s an incoming call.

597
01:02:52,530 --> 01:02:55,340
Do you perhaps have any problem with me, Chonlada?

598
01:02:56,400 --> 01:02:57,200
No, Boss.

599
01:03:02,130 --> 01:03:02,930
Liar.

600
01:03:04,560 --> 01:03:05,700
I’m not lying.

601
01:03:06,660 --> 01:03:08,500
I really don’t have any problem with you.

602
01:03:09,660 --> 01:03:11,160
Or do you want me to say otherwise?

603
01:03:19,300 --> 01:03:21,620
Your heart rate is too high.

604
01:03:24,000 --> 01:03:27,600
You want me to put this on so that you can check if I’m lying?

605
01:03:30,860 --> 01:03:34,260
Then don’t take it off if you have nothing to hide.

606
01:03:38,300 --> 01:03:39,500
Or are you afraid?

607
01:03:41,730 --> 01:03:47,100
I’m not. I don’t want to put it on because I think it’s nonsense.

608
01:03:59,160 --> 01:04:01,020
It might look nonsense to you.

609
01:04:01,820 --> 01:04:11,340
But to me, to have someone who seems close suddenly turns estranged and keeps avoiding me, it matters a lot.

610
01:04:17,900 --> 01:04:19,860
You probably imagine it, Boss.

611
01:04:20,330 --> 01:04:23,200
We have to work together every day, there’s no way I’d be able to avoid you.

612
01:04:25,060 --> 01:04:26,460
Now, if you’ll excuse me.

613
01:04:34,160 --> 01:04:35,760
If you insist I imagine it,

614
01:04:37,020 --> 01:04:41,500
then can we go out and have dinner together tonight?

615
01:04:44,800 --> 01:04:50,540
If you don’t like a fancy restaurant, we can have some noodles at the stall near your condo.

616
01:04:54,360 --> 01:04:56,060
I’m afraid I’ll have to turn down the offer.

617
01:04:56,860 --> 01:04:58,200
I already have another plan.

618
01:05:03,660 --> 01:05:06,500
See? I’m not lying.

619
01:05:15,960 --> 01:05:17,260
Please excuse me, Boss.

620
01:06:11,660 --> 01:06:13,580
[Boss Adisorn]

621
01:06:59,360 --> 01:07:01,700
If you’re staying late, I can stay and help.

622
01:07:02,700 --> 01:07:05,860
No need. You can go home.

623
01:07:06,460 --> 01:07:08,330
I think I’ll sleep here tonight…

624
01:07:09,460 --> 01:07:11,160
since I got turned down anyway.

625
01:07:11,730 --> 01:07:13,180
Your appointment got cancelled?

626
01:07:14,130 --> 01:07:15,820
But it’s not on your schedule, Boss.

627
01:07:17,760 --> 01:07:18,700
Never mind.

628
01:07:19,260 --> 01:07:20,180
It’s a last-minute one.

629
01:07:24,730 --> 01:07:25,530
Yes, Boss.

630
01:07:28,260 --> 01:07:32,660
By the way, Big Boss just called and said that you didn’t pick up his call.

631
01:07:34,530 --> 01:07:35,960
Tell him I’m busy.

632
01:07:37,200 --> 01:07:38,130
I have to get some work done.

633
01:07:38,730 --> 01:07:41,220
I told him exactly that.

634
01:07:41,260 --> 01:07:45,540
But he said there’ll be an important guest coming for dinner at your place tonight.

635
01:07:45,660 --> 01:07:50,140
And if you want to know who it is, you should take a look at his message.

636
01:08:04,780 --> 01:08:05,700
Is it urgent?

637
01:08:06,730 --> 01:08:08,020
No, Boss.

638
01:08:08,660 --> 01:08:09,620
I’ll do it tomorrow then.

639
01:08:10,900 --> 01:08:12,020
Shut down the air-con for me.

640
01:08:12,980 --> 01:08:14,340
See you tomorrow.

641
01:08:39,060 --> 01:08:40,260
[Next Episode]
Excuse me?

642
01:08:40,260 --> 01:08:43,260
[Pheempat]: The Watin Group is going to have a private event for a big group of customers.

643
01:08:43,260 --> 01:08:44,460
It must be ruined, Lada.

644
01:08:44,460 --> 01:08:45,740
I will wreck it!

645
01:08:45,740 --> 01:08:47,939
Chonlada! Chonlada!

646
01:08:48,420 --> 01:08:49,979
Please don’t do this, Boss.

647
01:08:49,979 --> 01:08:52,300
You have no idea how scared I am.

648
01:08:54,100 --> 01:08:56,380
[Nam]: I don’t know what it is that you fear.

649
01:08:57,540 --> 01:08:59,380
But if you’re worried about me,

650
01:09:00,220 --> 01:09:02,020
then don’t leave me.

651
01:09:02,939 --> 01:09:05,740
[Lada]: I’m going to tell Miss Apo everything and end this!

652
01:09:06,100 --> 01:09:07,580
Go on, I also want to know…

653
01:09:07,899 --> 01:09:10,779
what she’d say when she finds out you’re my sister.

654
01:09:11,460 --> 01:09:14,060
[Lada]: What you want between us is impossible.

655
01:09:18,660 --> 01:09:22,979
♫ Is this love? Is that what they call it?♫

656
01:09:22,979 --> 01:09:26,340
♫ When my heart starts to waver♫

657
01:09:26,340 --> 01:09:31,020
♫ Like a stream of water slowly pouring over my heart♫

658
01:09:31,020 --> 01:09:33,979
♫ From dusk till dawn, you’re never far from my sight♫

659
01:09:33,979 --> 01:09:38,660
♫ Or is this love? Are you that someone...♫

660
01:09:38,660 --> 01:09:42,180
♫ ...who’s destined to be with me?♫

661
01:09:42,180 --> 01:09:48,180
♫ Is this really happening ? I really want to know ♫

662
01:09:48,180 --> 01:09:52,380
♫‘Cos you now hold a special place in my heart♫

663
01:09:52,380 --> 01:09:57,460
♫Honestly, I can’t help but still doubt it♫

664
01:09:57,460 --> 01:10:04,860
♫Are you really that person my heart has been looking for?♫

665
01:10:09,020 --> 01:10:13,540
♫ Is this love? Is that what they call it?♫

666
01:10:13,540 --> 01:10:16,340
♫ When my heart starts to waver♫

667
01:10:16,420 --> 01:10:21,060
♫ Like a stream of water slowly pouring over my heart♫

668
01:10:21,100 --> 01:10:24,300
♫ From dusk till dawn, you’re never far from my thought♫

669
01:10:24,300 --> 01:10:28,740
♫ Or is this love? Are you that someone...♫

670
01:10:28,780 --> 01:10:32,100
♫ ...who’s destined to be with me?♫

671
01:10:32,100 --> 01:10:38,220
♫ Is this really happening ? I really want to know ♫

672
01:10:38,580 --> 01:10:44,420
♫‘Cos you now hold a special place in my heart♫

673
01:10:44,420 --> 01:10:47,580
[Waves of Deception]

